---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: "TOUR SCOUT Guide",
  description: "Your guide to using the AI-powered tour planning assistant"
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <main>
    <section class="py-16 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose dark:prose-invert">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Welcome to TOUR SCOUT</h1>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Getting Started</h2>

          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">1. Haven't Signed Up Yet?</h3>
              <p>Follow this link to create your account and unlock full access: 
                <a href="https://chatgpt.com/g/g-67e60e8bfa2481918f948a7e28905145-scout-the-tour-assistant" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">Sign Up Here</a>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">2. How to Log In to TOUR SCOUT</h3>
              <p>Use the same email you signed up with to access the GPT here: 
                <a href="https://chatgpt.com/g/g-67e60e8bfa2481918f948a7e28905145-scout-the-tour-assistant" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">Scout GPT</a>
              </p>
              <p class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2">
                Important: Your login is case-sensitive — make sure to type your email exactly as you did when signing up
              </p>
              <p class="text-base mt-2">If you're not seeing full access after logging in, try refreshing the window and entering your email again.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">3. Join the WhatsApp Beta Crew</h3>
              <p>This is where we drop quick tips, feature updates, sneak peeks, and let you vote on what Scout learns next.
                <a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 ml-2">Join the WhatsApp Crew</a>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">4. Start Strong — Quick Use Cases</h3>
              <p>Here's what beta users say they love using Scout for:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2">
                <li><strong>Show Day Rundown:</strong> Nearby food, errands, late night eats, wellness, driver hotels, etc.</li>
                <li><strong>Routing Help:</strong> Multi-city planning with stopover recs and drive times</li>
                <li><strong>Day Off Ideas:</strong> Chill spots, crew-friendly bars, walkable hotels, etc.</li>
                <li><strong>Production Vibes:</strong> Load-in logistics, errand runs, airport times</li>
                <li><strong>Mental Health Wins:</strong> Calm parks, sleep tips, and crew-first design</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2 italic">→ Just drop in your dates and cities. Scout does the rest.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">5. Pro Tip: Ask Scout Anything</h3>
              <p>Scout isn't just a location tool. It's a thinking partner. Have conversations with it about:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2">
                <li>Your tour struggles</li>
                <li>Managing mental health on the road</li>
                <li>Navigating career growth and transitions</li>
                <li>Learning tour skills or strategies you didn't even know you needed</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2">Whether you're solving a real problem or just thinking out loud — Scout's built to listen, adapt, and help. Scout's trained on real tour knowledge, not generic search results.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">6. Having Trouble Logging In?</h3>
              <p>Here's what to try if you're having issues accessing Scout — it's usually a quick fix:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2">
                <li>Double-check that you're using the same email you used to purchase access — it's case-sensitive, so type it in exactly as you did when signing up</li>
                <li>Try refreshing the page and re-entering your email when prompted</li>
                <li>Still stuck? Reach out to us directly at <a href="mailto:concertindustryhelp@gmail.com" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">concertindustryhelp@gmail.com</a> and we'll get you sorted fast</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">7. Payment & Account Help</h3>
              <p>Our payment system is handled by Auth Flow.</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2">
                <li>For any questions regarding your billing account, email <a href="mailto:support@authflow.ai" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">support@authflow.ai</a></li>
                <li>To cancel or manage your subscription, go to the original confirmation email from Auth Flow — it includes your personalized link to manage billing</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">8. You're helping shape the future of touring.</h3>
              <p class="text-xl">Thanks for jumping into the beta. See you in the chat. See you on the road. Let's make this smarter.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout> 